						               													<description>&amp;quot;In you&amp;#10;Alpha and Omega&amp;#10;Sleeplessly play&amp;#10;Hide-and-seek.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;- Sri Chinmoy, Pope John Paul II: God&amp;rsquo;s Heart-Prize winner, Agni Press, 2002&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hide-and-seek is a thematic game where players who are hiding will then close their eyes, while the player who has &amp;quot;it&amp;quot; is searching.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Searching is done by calling out loud the number of &amp;quot;it&amp;quot;'s current position. Hiding players who happen to be next to it have to revel themselves as shown. Players who think that &amp;quot;it&amp;quot; might be far away can at anytime decide to come out and run.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then a deck-building race to the safe spot ensues, with cards such as &amp;quot;leapfrog&amp;quot; (over an opponent) and &amp;quot;dash&amp;quot; (double move) and &amp;quot;climb&amp;quot; (double climbing this round. Some of the cards built into the deck and also be used while hiding, such as &amp;quot;distraction&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;mommy is coming&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;loose barking dog&amp;quot;. Players get points after each round, using them to get better cards for their deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is meant for both children and adults, and plays very much like an actual hide-and-seek outdoor game, but indoors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
